- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper focuses on analyzing social networks formed by interactions among Twitter users and inferring the support of each user to the presidential candidates. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper mentions the development of analytic tools combining natural language processing and machine learning classification to infer the opinion of Twitter users. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the content of tweets. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks): The paper analyzes social networks formed by interactions among Twitter users and infers the support of each user to the presidential candidates. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the potential of using social media data to predict social trends, which is a topic related to the intersection of computers and society.
